HEADWORD: Simulty
<hw>Sim"ul*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>simultas</ets> a hostile encounter, drudge, originally, a (hostile)
coming together, fr. <ets>simul</ets> together: cf. OF.
<ets>simult⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <def>Private grudge or quarrel;
<as>as, domestic <ex>simulties</ex></as>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>B. Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
